        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down.</hi> | Beckenham | <hi rend="print">Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>March 7<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Tyndall</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I wrote about a week ago, explaining that my D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Ogle was not the same as yours, &amp; asking whether he might call on you.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> But the two men may make all the difference to you.— As my man has been very obliging to me, I much wish to make him some answer.— Forgive me for bothering you.— Shall I say that you have not attended to odorous particles &amp; are sorry that you cannot give him the desired information?<ref target="#foot.f3"/> Or anything else you may determine on. I know how busy you must be.—</p>
<p>Yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 Beckenham] <hi rend="italic">before del</hi> ‘<hi rend="italic">Bromley.</hi>’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.6 else] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n3">1.6 may] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
